    "Integration of buildings with power grids, microgrids, and energy markets So far, we have discussed how modeling and control methods can be used to improve occupant comfort and increase the energy efficiency of buildings.",
    "However, buildings do not function in isolation and their operation can actually have significant impacts on other energy systems.",
    "The energy utilized in buildings come from power grids, and recently, from renewable sources installed at the local building/community level as well.",
    "In order to mitigate climate change, buildings must maximize their energy consumption from clean sources.",
    "One way that buildings can achieve the above is by providing load flexibility to facilitate clean energy sources such as wind and solar that have variable generation and cannot be controlled at will to meet electricity demand, a mechanism commonly called demand response (DR)."
  ],
